<div style="background-color: white; border-radius: 12px; padding: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px;">
<h2 style="color: #f09b08; font-size: 2.2em; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom: 3px solid #F09B08; padding-bottom: 15px;">1. Understanding What to Test</h2>
<p style="font-size: 1.1em; margin-bottom: 25px; color: #141312;">Before writing tests, you need to understand what should be tested. This is a crucial skill that many developers struggle with. AI can help you analyze code to identify testable behaviors and potential edge cases without just generating tests for you.</p>
<div style="background-color: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; padding: 25px; margin: 30px 0;">
<h3 style="color: #141312; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 20px;">We face a number of challenges when trying to figure out what to test:</h3>
<ul style="color: #141312; padding-left: 20px;">
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Identifying what to test: Recognizing all the behaviors that need testing</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Understanding edge cases: Knowing what could go wrong</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Testing priorities: Figuring out what to test first</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Test types: Understanding when to use unit vs. integration tests</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div style="background-color: #f8f9fa; border: 2px solid #F09B08; border-radius: 12px; padding: 30px; margin: 30px 0;">
<h3 style="color: #f09b08; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 20px;">Prompt 1: Behavior Analysis Questions</h3>
<details style="background-color: white; border-radius: 8px; margin: 20px 0; border-left: 5px solid #141312;">
