</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="background-color: white; border-radius: 12px; padding: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px;">
<h2 style="color: #f09b08; font-size: 2.2em; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom: 3px solid #F09B08; padding-bottom: 15px;">2. Improving a Single Test</h2>
<p style="font-size: 1.1em; margin-bottom: 25px; color: #141312;">Many developers start by writing simple "happy path" tests but struggle with making them robust. Instead of asking AI to generate many tests, focus on taking one test and improving it with AI guidance.</p>
<div style="background-color: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; padding: 25px; margin: 30px 0;">
<h3 style="color: #141312; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 20px;">What are the challenges when writing tests?</h3>
<ul style="color: #141312; padding-left: 20px;">
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Basic tests only: Writing only simple tests that donŌĆÖt catch real issues</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Hard-to-read tests: Creating tests that donŌĆÖt clearly show their intent</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Brittle tests: Writing tests that break when implementation details change</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Missing assertions: Not verifying all important aspects of the result</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div style="background-color: #f8f9fa; border: 2px solid #F09B08; border-radius: 12px; padding: 30px; margin: 30px 0;">
<h3 style="color: #f09b08; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 20px;">Prompt 1: Single Test Enhancement</h3>
<details style="background-color: white; border-radius: 8px; margin: 20px 0; border-left: 5px solid #141312;">
<summary style="color: #141312; font-size: 1.3em; padding: 25px; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; background-color: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; margin-bottom: 0;"><span style="color: #f09b08;">Ō¢╝</span> Prompt Template</summary>
<div style="padding: 25px; background-color: white;">
