<div style="background-color: white; border-radius: 12px; padding: 40px; margin-bottom: 40px;">
<h2 style="color: #f09b08; font-size: 2.2em; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 30px; border-bottom: 3px solid #F09B08; padding-bottom: 15px;">3. Learning Test-Driven Development</h2>
<p style="font-size: 1.1em; margin-bottom: 25px; color: #141312;">Test-Driven Development (TDD) is a powerful practice that can be challenging for beginners. Instead of having AI generate both tests and code, use it to guide you through the TDD process step by step, developing your own skills.</p>
<div style="background-color: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; padding: 25px; margin: 30px 0;">
<h3 style="color: #141312; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 20px;">TDD can be difficult in several ways:</h3>
<ul style="color: #141312; padding-left: 20px;">
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Starting with tests: Difficulty writing tests before implementation</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Small increments: Tendency to implement too much at once</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Red-Green-Refactor: Understanding the TDD workflow</li>
<li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Test evolution: Knowing how to evolve tests as code changes</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div style="background-color: #f8f9fa; border: 2px solid #F09B08; border-radius: 12px; padding: 30px; margin: 30px 0;">
<h3 style="color: #f09b08; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 20px;">Prompt 1: Guided TDD Practice</h3>
