<div style="background-color: #141312; color: white; border-radius: 12px; padding: 30px; margin: 30px 0;">
<h3 style="color: #f09b08; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 25px;">Common Pitfalls</h3>
<p style="font-size: 1.1em; margin-bottom: 25px;">Be aware of these common issues when using AI to help with testing:</p>
<div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 25px;">
<div style="background-color: rgba(240, 155, 8, 0.1); padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #F09B08;">
<h4 style="color: #f09b08; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.2em;">Pitfall: Letting AI Write All Your Tests</h4>
<p style="margin: 10px 0;">Solution:</p>
<p style="margin: 5px 0;">Use AI to guide your thinking process, not to replace it. Write the tests yourself after discussion.</p>
</div>
<div style="background-color: rgba(240, 155, 8, 0.1); padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #F09B08;">
<h4 style="color: #f09b08; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.2em;">Pitfall: Testing Everything at Once</h4>
<p style="margin: 10px 0;">Solution:</p>
<p style="margin: 5px 0;">Focus on one behavior or test at a time, improving it before moving on.</p>
</div>
<div style="background-color: rgba(240, 155, 8, 0.1); padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #F09B08;">
<h4 style="color: #f09b08; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.2em;">Pitfall: Focusing on Test Quantity Over Quality</h4>
<p style="margin: 10px 0;">Solution:</p>
<p style="margin: 5px 0;">Prioritize writing a few good tests rather than many superficial ones.</p>
</div>
<div style="background-color: rgba(240, 155, 8, 0.1); padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #F09B08;">
<h4 style="color: #f09b08; margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.2em;">Pitfall: Skipping Learning for Convenience</h4>
<p style="margin: 10px 0;">Solution:</p>
<p style="margin: 5px 0;">When tempted to have AI generate code, ask yourself what learning opportunity you might be missing.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
